  "text": "BPH has been extensively studied from ecological and physiological perspectives, but the molecular regulation mechanisms are poorly understood. At present, the genomic resources available for BPH are scarce. [CITATION_1] identified more than 37,000 expressed sequence tags (ESTs) in various BPH tissues and stages [CITATION_2] . Together with the nucleotide sequences obtained by NCBI searches, 37,312 BPH ESTs are available. These data provide useful information for transcriptional, proteomic, and gene functional analysis of BPH. Nevertheless, these genetic data are insufficient for elucidating the molecular mechanism of BPH in agricultural ecological systems.",
